cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper introduces a method for molecular de novo design using deep reinforcement learning, which involves training a generative model to generate molecules with desirable properties. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of computer vision techniques for analyzing molecular structures (cs.CV) and natural language processing techniques for representing molecules as sequences (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the method to chemical engineering (cs.CE).
